                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><xi:include href="../encodingdesc.xml" parse="xml"/></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_axær" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><form type="lemma"><orth>axær</orth></form><usg><lang/></usg><sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>страшный суд</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>last judgment</q></abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>потоп</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>flood</q></abv:tr></sense></sense><re><form type="lemma"><orth>axæri bon</orth></form><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>день страшного суда</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>doomsday</q></abv:tr></sense></re><abv:exampleGrp><abv:example><quote>axæri boni ficcagidær Totrazi furt Alibeg æma Soslanæn tuǧd woʒænæj</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>в день страшного суда будет прежде всего схватка Тотразова сына Алибега с Сосланом</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>on the day of the doomsday, first of all, the fight between Totrazʼs son Alibeg and Soslan will be</q></abv:tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>II 23</biblScope></bibl></abv:example></abv:exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru">Из <mentioned xml:lang="ar" extralang="fa"><lang/> <w>āḫir</w> <gloss><q>последний</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ar" extralang="fa"><w/> <gloss><q>конец</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ar" extralang="fa"><w>āḫir zamān</w> <gloss><q>конец мира</q></gloss></mentioned>; термин мусульманского круга (как <ref type="xr" target="#entry_qajmæt"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_aʒal"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_xæram"/> и др.); встречается и в других кавказских языках: <mentioned xml:lang="av"><lang/> <w>axir</w> <gloss><q>конец</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kbd"><lang/> <w>axər zaman</w> <gloss><q>светопреставление</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="krc-x-balkar"><lang/> <w>axrə, axər</w> <gloss><q>конец</q></gloss></mentioned>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">From <mentioned xml:lang="ar" extralang="fa"><lang/> <w>āḫir</w> <gloss><q>last</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ar" extralang="fa"><w/> <gloss><q>end</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ar" extralang="fa"><w>āḫir zamān</w> <gloss><q>end of the world</q></gloss></mentioned>; term of the Muslim environment (like <ref type="xr" target="#entry_qajmæt"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_aʒal"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_xæram"/> etc.); found in other Caucasian languages: <mentioned xml:lang="av"><lang/> <w>axir</w> <gloss><q>end</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kbd"><lang/> <w>axər zaman</w> <gloss><q>end of light</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="krc-x-balkar"><lang/> <w>axrə, axər</w> <gloss><q>end</q></gloss></mentioned>.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>